cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.CL 

This paper discusses the use of social networks and social filtering on Digg, which falls under the category of social media and social computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also touches upon social networks and their role in promoting stories, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). Additionally, the paper discusses information filtering, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and human-computer interaction, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing to analyze user comments, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
